@startuml
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam sequenceArrowColor #333333
skinparam sequenceParticipantBorderColor #333333
skinparam sequenceLifeLineBorderColor #CCCCCC

title Profile Update Flow - Two-Step with Preview

actor "Candidate" as Candidate
participant "Frontend" as FE
participant "CV Extraction Router\nPOST /candidates/cv/scan" as CVEndpoint
participant "Mistral API" as Mistral
participant "User Router\nPUT /users/{user_id}" as UserEndpoint
database "PostgreSQL" as DB

note over Candidate, DB
  PROFILE UPDATE WITH CV
  ===================
  Step 1: Scan CV (Preview) - User sees before saving
  Step 2: Save Profile - User confirms and saves
end note

== STEP 1: Scan CV (Preview) ==

note over Candidate, CVEndpoint
  USER UPLOADS NEW CV IN PROFILE FORM
  Wants to extract and preview data first
end note

Candidate ->> FE: Selects CV file\n+ clicks "Scan CV"
FE ->> CVEndpoint: POST /candidates/cv/scan\n(multipart/form-data + PDF file)

note over CVEndpoint
  Rate Limit: 5 requests/minute
  Processing: In-memory only (no storage)
end note

== Step 1a: Validate File ==

CVEndpoint ->> CVEndpoint: validate_pdf_file()

note right
  Check:
  - Content-Type: application/pdf
  - File extension: .pdf
  - File size: < 10MB
end note

alt Validation Failed
  CVEndpoint -->> FE: HTTP 400 Bad Request
  FE -->> Candidate: "Invalid file type/size"
else Validation Passed
end note

== Step 1b: Extract Text ==

CVEndpoint ->> CVEndpoint: extract_text_from_pdf()\n(Uses pdfplumber library)

note right
  Reads PDF content from memory
  Extracts text from all pages
end note

== Step 1c: Call Mistral API ==

CVEndpoint ->> Mistral: POST /chat/completions\n(CV text + extraction prompt)

note right
  System prompt instructs AI to extract:
  - profile (name, email, phone, summary)
  - experience (company, position, duration, description)
  - education (institution, degree, field, year)
  - skills (list of strings)
  - languages (list of strings)
  - certifications (name, issuer, year)
end note

Mistral -->> CVEndpoint: Structured JSON response

CVEndpoint ->> CVEndpoint: Parse JSON into\nCVExtractedData object

== Step 1d: Return Preview Data ==

CVEndpoint -->> FE: CVExtractionResponse\n(JSON with grouped extracted data)

note over FE
  Frontend displays:
  - Editable form with extracted fields
  - Profile section (name, email, phone, summary)
  - Experience section (company, position, duration, description)
  - Education section (institution, degree, field, year)
  - Skills list
  - Languages list
  - Certifications list
end note

FE -->> Candidate: Show extracted data in editable form

note over Candidate
  USER REVIEW PHASE:
  - Candidate reviews all extracted data
  - Edits any incorrect fields
  - Can cancel if not satisfied
  - Clicks "Save Profile" when ready
end note

== STEP 2: Save Profile ==

Candidate ->> FE: Reviews/edits data\n+ clicks "Save Profile"
FE ->> UserEndpoint: PUT /users/{user_id}\n(JSON body with user data + CV data)

note over UserEndpoint
  Request includes:
  - full_name, phone (standard fields)
  - summary, skills, languages (CV fields)
  - experience, education, certifications (CV fields)
end note

== Step 2a: Authorization Check ==

UserEndpoint ->> UserEndpoint: Check authorization

note right
  Rules:
  - Must be same user (self-update only)
  - Must be candidate role
end note

alt Not Authorized
  UserEndpoint -->> FE: HTTP 403 Forbidden
  FE -->> Candidate: "Not authorized"
else Authorized
end note

== Step 2b: Update User Data ==

UserEndpoint ->> DB: UPDATE users SET\nfull_name = ?, phone = ?\nWHERE id = ?
DB -->> UserEndpoint: Update success

== Step 2c: Update CV Data ==

note over UserEndpoint, DB
  Only updates if CV fields are provided
  Preserves existing data if not included
end note

UserEndpoint ->> DB: UPDATE candidate_info SET\ncv_extracted_profile = ?,\ncv_extracted_experience = ?,\ncv_extracted_education = ?,\ncv_extracted_skills = ?,\ncv_extracted_languages = ?,\ncv_extracted_certifications = ?\nWHERE user_id = ?
DB -->> UserEndpoint: Update success

== Step 2d: Return Success ==

UserEndpoint -->> FE: Success response\n(updated profile data)
FE -->> Candidate: "Profile updated successfully!"

note over Candidate
  BENEFITS OF TWO-STEP FLOW:
  - User sees extracted data before saving
  - Can edit/correct AI mistakes
  - No wasted Mistral API calls on cancel
  - Fast PUT (no AI call, just DB update)
end note

@enduml
